# Reader theme and Shiki

## UI theme (page chrome + markdown body)

- **Preset source of truth**: `src/theme/index.js` defines `BUILT_IN_THEMES` (currently `light`, `dark`). Default preset lives in `DEFAULT_SETTINGS.theme.preset` in `src/settings/index.js`.
- **CSS variables**: `applyThemeSettings()` / `createStyleVars()` apply vars to the viewer root; typography and layout use the same settings object.
- **Adding a preset**: Extend `BUILT_IN_THEMES` in `src/theme/index.js`, expose in popup reader UI if needed, then extend Shiki mapping in `shiki-config.js`.

## Shiki (fenced code colors)

- **Config** (`src/viewer/core/shiki-config.js`): `PRESET_TO_SHIKI_THEME_ID` must map every **reader preset key** to a bundled Shiki theme id. `SHIKI_BUNDLED_THEME_IDS` must list every Shiki id used in that map (for `createHighlighter({ themes })`). `SHIKI_LANG_IDS` is the web bundle language allowlist.
- **Whitespace normalization** (`src/viewer/core/shiki-highlighter.js`): `normalizeShikiPreWhitespace(pre)` removes whitespace-only text nodes Shiki inserts between `.line` spans so `white-space: pre` does not create blank lines while preserving tabs/indent.
- **Pipeline**: `renderDocument` ‚Üí optional `applyShikiToFencedCode` ‚Üí `sanitizeHtml()` in `src/viewer/core/renderer.js`. Shiki emits inline `style` on `pre`, `code`, and token spans; DOMPurify allows `style` via `ADD_ATTR` in the renderer‚Äôs purifier config.

## Full document re-render when theme changes

- Shiki bakes colors into HTML; updating CSS variables alone does not refresh fenced blocks.
- `MarkdownViewerApp.updateSettings()` now gates re-render via `needsFullRender()` in `src/shared/settings-diff.js`:
  - style-only changes (`typography.*`, `layout.contentMaxWidth`, `layout.showToc`, `layout.tocWidth`) skip full markdown render and only refresh reader styles/TOC state
  - theme preset and plugin/structure-affecting changes still require full `render()`

## Styles (`content.scss` via content script `?inline`)

- **Non-Shiki** fences: `pre:not(.shiki)` and `pre:not(.shiki) code` use theme vars (`--mdp-code-bg`, `--mdp-code-text`).
- **Shiki** fences: `pre.shiki` / `pre.shiki code` use `white-space: pre` and `tab-size: 4`; rely on `normalizeShikiPreWhitespace` rather than `white-space: normal` on `code`.
- **Specificity**: `.mdp-markdown-body pre.shiki code` must stay more specific than `.mdp-markdown-body code` so inline code `break-spaces` does not affect Shiki blocks.

## Build

- After changing Shiki config or viewer SCSS, run `npm run build`. Viewer SCSS is not exposed as standalone `web_accessible_resources`; it ships inside the content script bundle per `10-source-of-truth-build.mdc`.
